  "text": "A number of informatics-based approaches have been proposed as part of a systems strategy to prevent medical errors and improve patient safety. As clinicians increasingly use computer and Web-based resources, attention should be focused on ensuring that the design of the user interface itself does not predispose clinicians to making potential medical errors. Indeed, poorly designed user interfaces add cognitive demands on the users and their ability to perform tasks adequately [CITATION_1] , and potentially could lead to errors [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
